# Containerised CRUD REST API

## Project Description
A REST API with full CRUD functionality built with Node.js + Express, PostgreSQL database, and Nginx reverse proxy. Each service runs in a separate Docker container managed by Docker Compose.

## Tech Stack
- Node.js + Express (API)
- PostgreSQL (Database)
- Nginx (Reverse Proxy)
- Docker + Docker Compose

## How to Run
```bash
cp .env.example .env
docker compose up --build -d
```
API runs at: http://localhost

## Endpoints
- GET /api/items — Get all items
- POST /api/items — Create item
- PUT /api/items/:id — Update item
- DELETE /api/items/:id — Delete item
- GET /api/users — Get all users
- POST /api/users — Create user
- PUT /api/users/:id — Update user
- DELETE /api/users/:id — Delete user

